2006-09-07  Heiko Weiss  <heiko.weiss@de.trumpf-laser.com>

	* runtime/System/Private/NumberFormat/RoundTripFormatter.cs: 
	use general formatter for formatting since we do not support more than
	7 (Single) or 15 (Double) precision.
	Old code had bug formatting double 100.0, got 100. (with dot).

2006-09-01  Heiko Weiss  <heiko.weiss@de.trumpf-laser.com>

	* runtime/System/Private/NumberFormat/Formatter.cs: use general formatter
	instead of CustomFomatter if format string is empty.
	CustomFormatter is buggy if format string is empty (if formatting e.g. 0).

